news.title: Ahmedabad: Planners suggest wider roads to support taller buildings
news.para: ​In effect, the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) has suggested doing away with 6m, 9m and 12m roads in future town planning schemes. This is the first time this issue was discussed at a town planning committee meeting.

news.title: Indore: About 20 hectare land pooled so far for development of Pithampur sector 7
news.para: The existing industrial belt Pithampur, state’s largest industrial area, is expanded to attract fresh investments and accommodate more industries in the industrial belt.

news.title: Alliance Group plans to launch Rs 8,600 crore projects in Bengaluru, Chennai & Hyderabad
news.para: The company reported sales of Rs 2,290 crore for 2021-22 and sales of 3,686 homes, largely driven by the residential segment. “2021-22 was a remarkable year in our journey. In spite of the Covid-19 pandemic, we were able to cross many major milestones in the industry,” said Manoj Namburu, chairman, Alliance Group and Urbanrise.

news.title: Mysuru development body to regularise structures that have come up on notified land
news.para: Hundreds of acres of land that were acquired by Mysuru Urban Development Authority (Muda) for layout development and later were entangled in legal battle have been posing challenges to the urban body as structures have come up illegally.

news.title: Gurugram: Give flats in six months or pay 12% interest, builder told
news.para: Launched in 2008, ILD Greens in Sector 37C was to be delivered by 2013. But tower 2, which has 260 units, is still incomplete despite the allottees having paid around 90% of the dues. ILD Greens has a total of six towers, five of which have been completed.

news.title: About 125 houses on poramboke land in Tirupur demolished
news.para: The drive was carried out in the presence of a posse of police as nearly 300 residents, hailing from the Arunthathaiyar community, had staged protests against the move.

news.title: Tata Housing plans Rs 1,200 crore investment to acquire land for premium housing, plotted development
news.para: The company is open to go for outright acquisition of land parcels as well as forming joint development agreements (JDAs) with land owners. It is exploring land banks ranging from 12 acres to 200 acres.

news.title: Gujarat HC directs Ahmedabad civic body to act on breach of building bylaws
news.para: The AMC did not file its report on the action taken to ensure that the fire NOC and the BU permission were obtained by buildings. The AMC was directed to do so on February 25.

news.title: Housing sales up 9% during Jan-Mar across top eight cities: Knight Frank
news.para: "In the first quarter of 2022, 78,627 new homes were sold across the top eight cities which was higher by 9 per cent YoY (year-on-year) as against same time last year," the consultant said in a statement.

news.title: Land rates likely to see upward revision in Andhra Pradesh
news.para: The special chief secretary, revenue (excise, CT and registrations and stamp duties), Rajat Bhargava, has approved the proposals forwarded by the IG (stamps and registrations) V Ramakrishna, seeking the revision of land market values.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram district mops up 527 crore from property registration
news.para: Thiruvananthapuram was also the district to record the second highest number of documents to be registered in 2021-22. As many as 1,00,717 documents were registered in the district.

news.title: Anarock buys 75% stake in myHQ for Rs 125 crore
news.para: "We have acquired 75 per cent equity stake in myHQ in a cash and stock deal size of around Rs 125 crore. The amount also includes the fund infused by us for the growth of myHQ," said Anarock Chairman Anuj Puri.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body to offer 5% rebate on property tax
news.para: According to an official release issued by the GHMC commissioner, the scheme is applicable for the current financial and not for arrears accumulating from previous years.

news.title: Mysuru development body mulling over building vertical housing structures
news.para: Rajeev said, “It is not easy to distribute sites at these prices. Muda has accepted this fact, and is considering other options. Vertical housing structures seems like a viable solution for Mysuru city.”

news.title: Distribution of free e-patta starts in Tamil Nadu, 3.35 lakh people to benefit
news.para: In the past, the state government had extended free house site patta to thousands of people on lands taken over by the revenue, Adi Dravida and Tribal Welfare, BC and MBC and minorities welfare departments from individuals and unobjectionable government poramboke lands.
